data.name: Hearty Beef and Mushroom Lasagna
data.quickTastyDescription: A rich and flavorful lasagna layered with seasoned ground beef, mushrooms, and creamy béchamel sauce.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add chopped onions and minced garlic, sauté until softened.
Add the ground beef to the skillet and cook until browned, breaking it apart with a wooden spoon.
Stir in sliced mushrooms and cook until they are softened, about 5 minutes.
Add crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, beef broth, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. Simmer for 15-20 minutes to let the flavors meld.
In a separate bowl, mix ricotta cheese with a pinch of salt and pepper.

In a large baking dish, spread a layer of the meat sauce, followed by a layer of lasagna noodles. Spread a layer of ricotta cheese, then sprinkle with mozzarella cheese. Repeat the layers until all ingredients are used, finishing with a layer of meat sauce topped with mozzarella and parmesan cheese.
Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes. Then, uncover and bake for an additional 15-20 minutes or until the cheese is bubbly and golden brown.
Let it cool for 10 minutes before slicing. Garnish with fresh basil before serving.
